Following is a summary of the passenger traffic
and capacity statistics from International Consolidated Airlines Group
formed from the merger of British Airways and Iberia:  NOTE: Figures are preliminary and can be subsequently revised.  * = Available Seat Kilometer (ASKs) is the number of seats  available multiplied by the number of kilometers flown.  ** = Revenue Passenger-Kilometers  *** = Load Factor measures the capacity utilization or number  of seats used out of the total available.  Source: IAG International Airlines Group  To contact the reporter on this story:
